    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "mrEvr",
      "x": 1528,
      "y": 1098,
      "name": "ss1Note",
      "width": 0,
      "height": 0,
      "content": "Invite to Interview → sends emails to the candidates as a follow-up of applications at the interview stage.\n\nThe hiring pipeline in the candidate-details frame advances when this action is triggered."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "hKhs0",
      "x": -657,
      "y": 8721,
      "name": "testsNote",
      "width": 500,
      "height": 380,
      "content": "🧪 TESTS MANAGEMENT SECTION\n(beyond original DASH-06 scope — added to design)\n\nThese frames extend the dashboard beyond the original 5 views:\n• tests — /dashboard/tests — test library (view all tests)\n• test-details — /dashboard/tests/[id] — analytics + usage stats\n• test-edit — /dashboard/tests/[id]/edit — edit test questions/modules\n• test-edit-success — success modal after saving edits\n• test-share-modal — share test link modal (copy + send)\n• Add Question Modal — modal for adding questions during editing\n\n📌 This adds a 6th dashboard area not in REQUIREMENTS.md (DASH-01 to DASH-06 only covers build-test). Consider whether to add a DASH-07 requirement or treat this as an extension of DASH-06.\n\n📌 test-edit and test-share-modal are positioned at x:1624 on canvas (right of main column)."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "HshZ0",
      "x": -532,
      "y": 4407,
      "name": "buildTestFlowNote",
      "width": 500,
      "height": 320,
      "content": "🏗️ BUILD-TEST: MULTI-PAGE FLOW\n(original plan: all steps on one page; design uses separate frames per step)\n\nThe build-test flow is now designed as separate frames:\n• build-test — Step 1: Role selection\n• build-test-modules — Step 2: Module selection\n• build-test-custom-questions — Step 3: Custom questions (+ Add Question Modal)\n• build-test-generate — Step 4: Generate test\n• build-test-preview — Preview before publishing\n• build-test-success — 'Test Ready' success confirmation\n\n📌 DASH-06 note says 'all steps single page' — the design instead shows a multi-step page flow. Phase 5 implementers: decide between single-page stepper vs. multi-route flow. Either is valid; the frames show the content of each step regardless."
    },
    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "JKsEU",
      "x": -593,
      "y": -1833,
      "name": "missingMobileNote",
      "width": 500,
      "height": 380,
      "content": "⚠️ MISSING FRAMES — REQUIRED BEFORE PHASE 5\n\nMobile frames (375px) not yet designed:\n• dashboard--mobile (bottom tab bar 56px + card stack)\n• candidates-detail--mobile\n• compare--mobile (stacked columns)\n• talent-pool--mobile (1-col card stack)\n• build-test--mobile (vertical stepper, full-width CTAs)\n\nState variant frames not yet designed:\n• dashboard--skeleton (table rows = Skeleton shimmer)\n• talent-pool--skeleton (card grid = Skeleton shimmer)\n• dashboard--empty (EmptyState component centered in table area)\n\nAlso missing: candidates list frame is named 'candidates' in design but was not in the original plan naming convention. Treat it as the main /dashboard Candidates list view (DASH-01).\n\nDesign all missing frames before Phase 5 begins."
    },
